        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 21 at 5:29PM CDT until July 21 at 6:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Carson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southeastern Hutchinson County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northwestern Gray County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Southwestern Roberts County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 615 PM CDT.

* At 529 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Kingsmill, or
6 miles west of Pampa, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect some tree damage. Damage is likely to mobile
homes, roofs, and outbuildings.

* Locations impacted include...
Pampa, White Deer, Skellytown, Kingsmill, and Codman.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
